# Python Dev Standards (AI-friendly + reproducible)

## Structure (when adding Python code)

- **Code**: `src/<pkg>/` (importable package, no “scripts” blob)
- **Layers**: `models/`, `services/`, `controllers/`, `utils/` (small, explicit modules)
- **Tests**: `tests/` mirrors `src/<pkg>/` (pytest)
- **Config**: `configs/` for non-secret YAML/TOML; secrets via env vars (`.env` local only)

### This repo’s pipeline module map (mirror `README.md`)

When implementing the project outline, keep modules aligned to the pipeline steps:

```text
src/<pkg>/
├── controllers/
│   └── main.py                  # CLI entrypoint (reads config, orchestrates pipeline)
├── services/
│   ├── data_loader.py           # loads Dataset/*.csv → dataframe
│   ├── preprocessing.py         # cleaning/normalization → resumes_clean.parquet
│   ├── variant_generator.py     # generates variants → variants.parquet
│   ├── scoring/
│   │   ├── tfidf.py
│   │   ├── bm25.py
│   │   └── embeddings.py        # optional
│   ├── evaluation.py            # rank shift / top-k / thresholds → eval_summary
│   ├── logistic_regression.py   # analysis
│   └── visualization.py         # figures
├── models/
│   ├── config.py                # typed config schema
│   └── artifacts.py             # typed paths + artifact metadata
└── utils/
    ├── io.py                    # atomic writes, mkdirs, hashing
    ├── logging.py               # structured logging setup
    └── seeding.py               # deterministic seeds across libs
```

Naming: keep artifact filenames consistent with the README (`resumes_clean.parquet`, `variants.parquet`, `variants_scored.csv`, `eval_summary`).

Example:

